fields.value: Latent temporal shapes underlie the morphological evolution of leaves throughout the genus Vitis

dsDescriptionValue.value: This is a set of leaf images collected from vines of various species in the genus Vitis from the USDA germplasm repository in Geneva, NY. The images show the abaxial side of leaves collected from a single shoot per vine. The file name indicates the vine ID and the appended letter indicates which image of the series the file represents for that vine. Next to each leaf is a label indicating the node position from which the leaf was sampled (as measured in plastochrons from the tip of the shoot) as well as organ identity ("C", cluster; "T", tendril; "N", no organ).
